at|mitche:  Bidding:  Let's begin with a reminder of what a reverse is.  A REVERSE is a non-jump rebid (usually by opener) 
at a level higher than 2 of his / her first bid suit.  So 2@h by North was a reverse.
Here is the rule of reverses in 2 over 1. If responder did not make a 2 over 1 (game-forcing response), then a 
reverse shows a strong hand, at least 17 points.
Steve Robinson says the sequence 1@D - 1@S / 2@h promises longer @D than @h, usually 5-4.
There are exceptions to this principle, but they're not all that common.|
