at|mitche:  I haven't talked a lot about partnerships, so please excuse my introducing the conversation this late 
in the evening.
Your most valuable asset at the table is your partner.  S/he has to trust your signals and that your bids show what your 
agreements say they should.
Most partners will be pretty tolerant of an occasional misbid or failure to lead their suit when they overcall, 
but fact is that the best way to ruin your reputation at the table is to break partnership agreements with regularity, or 
to "operate."|
